    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">I bid 0-2, depends on the shadow im facing. Usually try to go from first site to site 3, except if you face nazguls and their Ford. Dont ever play out too much, because this is a twilight denial deck, but always try to play for 2 twilights, Aragorn removes them. Elrond is the healer, and he is also useful equipped with Vilya. Galdor is great, especially in a twilight denial deck, because if I remove a left over big minion (like Lurtz, Cave Troll, Witch-king etc..) I can walk forward and he wont be able to play him again because of low twilight. An example, I move to the Bridge, give the opponent 9 twilights and he plays an Uruk Scout and Lurtz. After the skirmishes the scout is dead, and Lurtz is without wounds. I exert Galdor, and Lurtz returns to owners hand. Then I walk forward, and give him 6 twilights (because of No Stranger or A Talent) and...no Lurtz!<br />
<br />
Shadow is uruk beatdown, nothing special about that. Troops are great, play 4 of them. Savagery punishes bigger fellowships, and Berserker punishes burdens. Saruman is great, maybe the best card from RotEL, all Uruks fierce means alot of wounds. Raiders work well together with Tower Assassins, especially with all the new allies from RotEL. A fierce strength 9 minion for 2 twilights is not so bad. <br />
 </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
